💼 Real DevOps Scenario

Suppose you need to verify every morning that essential services are running.

You could automate it with a script:

#!/bin/bash

SERVICES=("ssh" "nginx")

for SERVICE in "${SERVICES[@]}"
do
    if systemctl is-active --quiet "$SERVICE"
    then
        echo "$SERVICE : Running"
    else
        echo "$SERVICE : Stopped"
    fi
done

Instead of manually checking each service, one script performs the task consistently.

🚨 Biggest Mistakes Engineers Make
❌ Not quoting variables

Bad:

echo $NAME

Preferred:

echo "$NAME"

Quoting helps avoid issues with spaces and special characters.

❌ Ignoring exit codes

Always consider whether important commands succeeded before continuing.

❌ Hardcoding values

Instead of:

USER=anil

accept input or pass arguments where appropriate to make scripts reusable.

